text: Hi, does anyone have any ideas as to why the mobile hamburger menu on this site won’t collapse? <http://activevideo-6582663.hs-sites.com/-temporary-slug-9e827288-9d99-464c-9799-144f13677b3c?hs_preview=ZshEPQqg-23407450713>
My guess is that it's missing the some of the vast.js file or the CSS that helps it function. I don't even see the hamburger menu toggle appearing so I think it's the CSS.

We have some published landing pages for downloading content that are now being generated using HubDB dynamic pages. We want to  make sure the dynamic pages are always used but we don’t want to lose the analytics of the older landing pages. Does any one have best practices for going about this?

I’m 99% sure this isn’t possible (1% uncertainty because there are some pretty brilliant developers here who might have some ideas for you). Best bet may be to simply use those old LPs for comparison purposes until enough time has passed for them to be less relevant. You won’t _lose_ any of the analytics on those old pages, though I suspect you’re wanting to see them in one place rather than hopping between them.
